>h2 Assembler and Loader Commands
>tree Assembler and Loader Commands
Command forms verified in the shell:
- `as file.asm`
- `as -o output file.asm`
- `cupidasm file.asm`
- `cupidasm file.asm -o output`
- `cupidasm -o output file.asm`
- `exec /path/to/binary`
- `exec -d /path/to/binary`

>button ls /demos | shell:ls /demos
>button as /demos/hello.asm | shell:as /demos/hello.asm
>endtree

>h2 Script Files
>tree Script Files
Shipped `.cup` scripts can be run through `cupid` or by direct shell shortcut.

Example:
  cupid /bin/build.cup
  /bin/build.cup

>button Show build.cup | shell:cat /bin/build.cup
>endtree

>h2 Hotkeys
>tree Hotkeys
Source-backed shell hotkey:
- F7 in shell/Terminal -> `godspeak`

Desktop/global app hotkeys are documented in the desktop docs; this page keeps
the shell-facing command behavior only.
>endtree

